Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
import_module_model(25.10)                          import_module_model(25.10)

Name
       import_module_model - Imports library files into the iHDB structure

Syntax
       import_module_model

       [-help]

       -cell <string>

       [-idx_pair <string>]

       -inputs <string>

       -libs [-link_only]

       [-rc_corner <string>]

       [-tag <string>]

       -type {lib lef qrc_tech qrc_conf}

       Imports library files into the iHDB structure.

Parameters
       -cell< string>
              Specifies the cell to import.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each import_module_model parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man import_module_model

       -idx_pair <string>
              Specifies the idx pair list if the files are copied from the idx
              database.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -inputs <string>
              Specifies the full path of the input file to be imported.

              Note:  The  import_module_model  command  supports the import of
              Quantustm Extraction Solution input files.

              Data_type: string, required

       -libs  Specifies whether input file is a library file or not.

              Note: This option should be used for type lef, lib, qrc_tech, or
              qrc_conf.

              Note: The library files:

              * *.lib are saved at <iHDB>/<cell>/.libs/mmmc/

              * *.lef  are saved at <iHDB>/<cell>/.libs/lef/

              *
                 qrcTechFile are  saved  at  <iHDB>/<cell>/.libs/mmmc/<rc_cor-
                ner>/qrcTechFile

              * qrc.conf are saved at <iHDB>/<cell>/.libs/qx/qrc.conf

              Note:  The  following  GDS related model types can be saved with
              -libs option:

              * gds_map

              * stream_libs

              * stream_layermap

              Data_type: bool, required

       -link_only
              Creates a link or actual hard copy.

              Note: If the -link_only parameter  is  specified,  then  a  link
              pointing  to the current library location is created. If  is the
              -link_only parameter is not specified then the  actual  physical
              file will be there.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -rc_corner <string>
              Specifies the list of RC corners.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -tag <string>
              Specifies a tag of a saved file.

              Note: The -tag and -libs parameters are mutually exclusive.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -type {lib lef qrc_tech qrc_conf}
              Specifies  the  type(s)  of  module model. The model type can be
              lib, lef, qrc_tech, or qrc_conf.

              Default:

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The following command imports a LEF file:

                import_module_model  -cell  tdsp_core  -libs  -type  lef  -in-
                put_file                                            /icd/hier-
                flow2/DATA2/tdsp_core/init/pnr/tdsp_core.enc.dat/libs/lef/*.lef

              * The following command imports streamOut layer  map  into  cell
                top_die:

                import_module_model     -cell     top_die     -inputs    ./in-
                put_data/lvs_data/streamOut.layermap -libs  -type  stream_lay-
                ermap

                This  will  be saved into <iHDB_root>/top_die/.libs/steam_lay-
                ermap/steamOut.layermap

